  • I create one table for using in my quaries.
  • This table has just comedy movies(without TV Series).
  • I filter movies type to be comedy but not to be Reality-TV, Documentary or Short
is_exist <- dbExistsTable(con, "just_movies")
is_exist
## [1] TRUE
dbGetQuery(con,"DROP TABLE just_movies
;"
)
## data frame with 0 columns and 0 rows
dbGetQuery(con,"CREATE TABLE just_movies AS
WITH just_comedies AS
(
    SELECT * FROM
    title_basics
    where 
    genres like '%Comedy%' 
    and genres not like '%Reality-TV%'
    and genres not like '%Documentary%'
    and genres not like '%Short%'
    and genres not like '%Animation%'
    and genres not like '%Drama%'
)
select jc.* 
from just_comedies jc 
left join title_episode te on jc.tconst=te.tconst
where te.tconst is null
;"
)
## data frame with 0 columns and 0 rows
is_exist <- dbExistsTable(con, "just_movies")
is_exist
## [1] TRUE
  • I try to find best comedy movie directors
  • I take director which has more than 5 movies and average number of votes for movies is bigger than 1500. Also each movie has more than 1000 votes.
  • I take movies which runtime between 80 and 120 minutes. _ I order them averageratings.
query.imdb.best.comedy.director <- dbGetQuery(con,"
WITH summary AS
(
   select nb.nconst,
   primaryname,
   birthyear,
   tc.tconst,
   tr.averagerating,
   tr.numvotes,
   tb.genres 
   from
   name_basics nb
   join title_crew tc on nb.nconst = tc.directors
   join title_ratings tr on tc.tconst = tr.tconst
   join just_movies jm on tc.tconst = jm.tconst
   join title_basics tb on tc.tconst = tb.tconst
   where tb.runtimeminutes between 80 and 120 ---for run time minutes
)
select primaryname,birthyear,
avg(averagerating) as averagerating,
avg(numvotes) as avgnumvotes, 
count(*) as numberofmovies
from summary
where numvotes > 1000 --- for number of votes per movie
and birthyear >=1950 --- for director birth year
group by primaryname,birthyear
having count(*)>5 --- director must have at least 5 movie
and avg(numvotes)>1500 --- average number of votes at least 1500
order by avg(averagerating) desc
limit 20"
)

query.imdb.best.comedy.director.movies <- dbGetQuery(con,"
WITH summary AS
(
   select 
   primaryname,
   startyear,
   endyear,
   jm.primarytitle,
   tr.averagerating,
   tr.numvotes,
   genres 
   from
   name_basics nb
   join title_crew tc on nb.nconst = tc.directors
   join title_ratings tr on tc.tconst = tr.tconst
   join just_movies jm on tc.tconst = jm.tconst
)
select *
from summary
where primaryname in ('Robert Zemeckis','Carlo Verdone','Todd Phillips') --- i am writing names here, i 
order by averagerating desc
limit 20
"
)
